snippet.textDisplay:
As much as I've loved the songs CS has released this season, I have to say that there is no replacing this kind of real music. No electronic sounds, just pure musical and singing talent. This is who we are at the core as a culture. We need more talent like Kaavish, pure heart and soul. Trends and commercial success come and go but talent like their's survives the ages. There's a reason people still keep going to the classic CS songs. I hope that that CS team keep this in mind for next season. The younger generation needs to be introduced to genuine music and classical singing. It is what distinguishes us from other cultures and makes us unique. We don't need to imitate others in order to stand out, the cultural treasure trove we already possess far supercedes any latest trend. 
I know it has been mentioned several times already but Kaavish should've been given more time on this track. This is a beautiful song but it left me wanting....
